TITLE: Closing Knex Instance to Prevent Hanging
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to properly close a Knex instance after execution to prevent the Node process from hanging due to open connections. It wraps the migration process in a `try...catch...finally` block and uses `knex.destroy()` in the `finally` block to ensure the connection is closed regardless of whether the migration succeeds or fails.
SOURCE: https://github.com/knex/documentation/blob/main/src/faq/recipes.md#_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
async function migrate() {
  try {
    await knex.migrate.latest({/**config**/})
  } catch (e) {
    process.exit(1)
  } finally {
    try {
      knex.destroy()
    } catch (e) {
      // ignore
    }
  }
}

migrate()
```

