TITLE: Initializing Knex with MSSQL and Custom Type Mapping
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates configuring Knex with MSSQL and defining a custom `mapBinding` function. The function maps Knex query parameters to `tedious` types, allowing custom type handling. This example binds all strings to varchar and allows passing tedious type at query time.
SOURCE: https://github.com/knex/documentation/blob/main/src/guide/index.md#_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { TYPES } from 'tedious';

const knex = require('knex')({
  client: 'mssql',
  connection: {
    options: {
      mapBinding: value => {
        // bind all strings to varchar instead of nvarchar
        if (typeof value === 'string') {
          return {
            type: TYPES.VarChar,
            value
          };
        }

        // allow devs to pass tedious type at query time
        if (value != null && value.type) {
          return {
            type: value.type,
            value: value.value
          };
        }

        // undefined is returned; falling back to default mapping function
      }
    }
  }
});
```

