TITLE: Knex Transaction without Handler Function (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to create a transaction instance without a handler function, allowing for deferred execution of statements within the transaction. Requires explicit commit or rollback.
SOURCE: https://github.com/knex/documentation/blob/main/src/guide/transactions.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// Using trx as a transaction object:
const trx = await knex.transaction();

const books = [
  {title: 'Canterbury Tales'},
  {title: 'Moby Dick'},
  {title: 'Hamlet'}
];

trx('catalogues')
  .insert({name: 'Old Books'}, 'id')
  .then(function(ids) {
    books.forEach((book) => book.catalogue_id = ids[0]);
    return trx('books').insert(books);
  })
  .then(trx.commit)
  .catch(trx.rollback);
```

