TITLE: Nesting JSON Functions - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates nesting JSON functions, such as `jsonRemove` and `jsonSet`, directly from the knex object within a `jsonExtract` call. This example removes the '$.min' and '$.max' properties from the 'population' column, sets '$.current' to '1234', and extracts each result with different aliases.
SOURCE: https://github.com/knex/documentation/blob/main/src/guide/query-builder.md#_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
knex('cities')
  .jsonExtract([
    [
      knex.jsonRemove('population', '$.min'), 
      '$', 
      'withoutMin'
    ],
    [
      knex.jsonRemove('population', '$.max'), 
      '$', 
      'withoutMax'
    ],
    [
      knex.jsonSet('population', '$.current', '1234'),
      '$',
      'currentModified',
    ]
  ])
```

