TITLE: Cross Join with Knex.js
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates cross join operations using Knex.js.  The cross join creates all possible combinations of rows from 'users' and 'accounts' tables. Cross join conditions are only supported in MySQL and SQLite3.
SOURCE: https://github.com/knex/documentation/blob/main/src/guide/query-builder.md#_snippet_143

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
knex.select('*')
  .from('users')
  .crossJoin('accounts')

knex.select('*')
  .from('users')
  .crossJoin('accounts', 'users.id', 'accounts.user_id')

knex.select('*')
  .from('users')
  .crossJoin('accounts', function() {
    this
      .on('accounts.id', '=', 'users.account_id')
      .orOn('accounts.owner_id', '=', 'users.id')
  })
```

