TITLE: Knex.js Configuration with MJS Extension
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript snippet demonstrates a Knex.js configuration file using the `.mjs` extension. It shows how to specify the `loadExtensions` property to include `.mjs` files for migrations when using ESM. This is important for Knex to find the migration files.
SOURCE: https://github.com/knex/documentation/blob/main/src/guide/migrations.md#_snippet_26

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
/** 
 * knexfile.mjs
 */
export default {
  migrations: {
    // ... client, connection,etc ....
    directory: './migrations',
    loadExtensions: ['.mjs'] // 
  }
}
```

