TITLE: onNotExists Clause with Knex.js
DESCRIPTION: Adds an `onNotExists` clause to a join in Knex.js. The query joins 'users' and 'contacts', filtering for cases where no corresponding 'accounts' record exists with 'users.account_id = accounts.id'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/knex/documentation/blob/main/src/guide/query-builder.md#_snippet_150

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
knex.select('*').from('users').join('contacts', function() {
  this
    .on('users.id', '=', 'contacts.id')
    .onNotExists(function() {
      this.select('*')
        .from('accounts')
        .whereRaw('users.account_id = accounts.id');
    })
})
```

