TITLE: onNotBetween Clause with Knex.js
DESCRIPTION: Adds an `onNotBetween` clause to a join in Knex.js. The code joins 'users' and 'contacts' tables, filtering for records where 'contacts.id' is NOT between 5 and 30.
SOURCE: https://github.com/knex/documentation/blob/main/src/guide/query-builder.md#_snippet_152

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
knex.select('*').from('users').join('contacts', function() {
  this
    .on('users.id', '=', 'contacts.id')
    .onNotBetween('contacts.id', [5, 30])
})
```

