TITLE: Adding Row Number with Knex.js
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to add a row_number() call to your query using the `.rowNumber()` method in Knex.js. String, Raw and Function syntax is supported.
SOURCE: https://github.com/knex/documentation/blob/main/src/guide/query-builder.md#_snippet_88

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
knex('users')
  .select('*')
  .rowNumber('alias_name', 'email', 'firstName')
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
knex('users')
  .select('*')
  .rowNumber(
    'alias_name', 
    ['email', 'address'], 
    ['firstName', 'lastName']
  )
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
knex('users')
  .select('*')
  .rowNumber(
    'alias_name', 
    knex.raw('order by ??', ['email'])
  )
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
knex('users')
  .select('*')
  .rowNumber('alias_name', function() {
    this.orderBy('email').partitionBy('firstName')
  })
```

