TITLE: Executing Raw SQL with Encryption Key in SQLite with Knex
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to execute a raw SQL statement to set the encryption key for an SQLCipher database when not using `afterCreate` within the pool. This approach requires executing the `PRAGMA KEY` statement before every SQL query, which can be less efficient than setting it up during connection creation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/knex/documentation/blob/main/src/faq/recipes.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
return knex.raw("PRAGMA KEY = 'secret'")
  .then(() => knex('some_table')
    .select()
    .on('query-error', function(ex, obj) {
      console.log(
        "KNEX select from some_table ERR ex:", 
        ex, 
        "obj:", 
        obj
      );
    })
  );
```

